						<summary>

						<p>Pillar [No. 1] on top of the Fort to the north of the old village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the death by <hi rend="italic">samādhividhi</hi> of Śubhanandi, disciple of Dēvēndra Siddhāntamunīśvara. It is not dated but palaeographically assignable to about the 11th century A.D.</p>						

